article.headline: (19) TEMPLE 81, HAMPTON 38
article.story:
HAMPTON, Virginia (Ticker) -- Candice Dupree scored 20 points 
and Kamesha Hairston added 16 as No. 19 Temple used a sizzling
shooting performance for an 81-38 victory over Hampton.

Making 55 percent (18-of-33) of their attempts in the first
half, the Owls (5-0) raced to a 43-25 lead at the half.

Despite the big lead, Temple turned up the defensive pressure in
the second, holding Hampton to just 13 points on four baskets.
Overall, it forced 24 turnovers and blocked 12 shots.

Dupree, who had four blocks, shot 9-of-13 from the field and
Khadija Bowens chipped in eight points and seven assists.

Reserve Monica Rogers scored nine points for Hampton (0-4),
which had its starters combine for just 17 points while shooting
27 percent (7-of-26).
